{{NCAATeamSeason |Mode=Basketball |Year=2009â10 |Prev year=2008â09 |Next year=2010â11 |Team=Northwestern Wildcats |Image=Northwestern N logo.gif |Conference=Big Ten Conference |Division= |ShortConference= Big Ten |CoachRank= |APRank= |Record=20&ndash;14 |ConfRecord=7&ndash;11 |HeadCoach=[[Bill Carmody]] |AsstCoach1=Mitch Henderson |AsstCoach2=Tavaras Hardy |AsstCoach3=Ivan Vujic |Director of Basketball Operations=John Davidson |Graduate Manager=Mike Pepple |Senior Manager=Daniel Blumenthal |Trainer=Lanny Bradford |StadiumArena=[[Welsh-Ryan Arena]] |Champion= |BowlTourney=[[2010 National Invitation Tournament|NIT]] |BowlTourneyResult=First Round }} {{2009â10 Big Ten men's basketball standings}} The '''2009â10 [[Northwestern Wildcats men's basketball]] team''' represented [[Northwestern University]] in the [[2009â10 NCAA Division I men's basketball season|2009â10]] [[college basketball]] season. This was head coach [[Bill Carmody]]'s tenth season at the Northwestern. The Wildcats are members of the [[Big Ten Conference]] and played their home games at [[Welsh-Ryan Arena]]. They finished the season 20&ndash;14, 7&ndash;11 in Big Ten play, lost in the quarterfinals of the [[2010 Big Ten Conference Men's Basketball Tournament]] and were invited to the [[2010 National Invitation Tournament]] where they lost in the first round to the [[University of Rhode Island]]. The Wildcats received its first national (AP) ranking in 41 years, when it was ranked #25 in the December 28th AP poll.
